@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy — CloudZen</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="CloudZen Privacy Policy — how we collect, use, and protect your information." />
</HeadContent>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24">

        @* ── Header ── *@
        <header class="mb-10">
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
                Last updated: April 6, 2026
            </p>
        </header>

        @* ── Table of Contents ── *@
        <nav class="legal-toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
            <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-500 mb-3">Contents</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 text-sm">
                <li><a href="/privacy#information-we-collect" class="legal-toc-link">Information We Collect</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#how-we-use" class="legal-toc-link">How We Use Your Information</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#third-party-services" class="legal-toc-link">Third-Party Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#cookies" class="legal-toc-link">Cookies &amp; Local Storage</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#data-retention" class="legal-toc-link">Data Retention</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#your-rights" class="legal-toc-link">Your Rights</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#childrens-privacy" class="legal-toc-link">Children's Privacy</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#security" class="legal-toc-link">Security</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#changes" class="legal-toc-link">Changes to This Policy</a></li>
                <li><a href="/privacy#contact" class="legal-toc-link">Contact Us</a></li>
            </ol>
        </nav>

        @* ── Introduction ── *@
        <div class="legal-body">
            <p>
                CloudZen Inc. ("<strong>CloudZen</strong>," "we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy
                explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website at
                <a href="https://www.cloud-zen.net" class="legal-link">cloud-zen.net</a> and use our services.
            </p>
            <p>
                By using our website, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you
                do not agree, please discontinue use of our website.
            </p>

            @* ── 1. Information We Collect ── *@
            <h2 id="information-we-collect" class="legal-heading">1. Information We Collect</h2>

            <h3 class="legal-subheading">Information You Provide Directly</h3>
            <p>We collect information you voluntarily submit through our website:</p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>
                    <strong>Contact Form</strong> — your name, email address, subject, and message when you reach out to us.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Appointment Booking</strong> — your selected date, time slot, timezone, and any optional details
                    you provide when scheduling a consultation.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Chatbot Conversations</strong> — the messages you exchange with our AI-powered chatbot during your
                    visit. Conversations are processed in real time and are not stored after your session ends.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="legal-subheading">Information Collected Automatically</h3>
            <p>When you access our website, we may automatically collect certain technical information:</p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>
                    <strong>Usage &amp; Telemetry Data</strong> — page views, session duration, browser type, operating system,
                    and referring URLs collected through Azure Application Insights for performance monitoring and error
                    diagnostics.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>IP Address &amp; Correlation IDs</strong> — used for rate limiting, security, and to correlate
                    diagnostic logs. IP addresses are not linked to personally identifiable profiles.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="legal-subheading">Information We Do Not Collect</h3>
            <p>
                We do not collect payment card numbers, social security numbers, government-issued IDs, or any other sensitive
                financial or identity documents through this website. If a project engagement requires payment processing, it is
                handled through separate, PCI-compliant channels.
            </p>

            @* ── 2. How We Use Your Information ── *@
            <h2 id="how-we-use" class="legal-heading">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>Respond to your inquiries and contact requests.</li>
                <li>Schedule and manage consultation appointments.</li>
                <li>Provide real-time chatbot assistance about our services.</li>
                <li>Monitor and improve website performance, reliability, and security.</li>
                <li>Diagnose technical issues and prevent abuse.</li>
                <li>Comply with legal obligations when required.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for their
                marketing purposes.
            </p>

            @* ── 3. Third-Party Services ── *@
            <h2 id="third-party-services" class="legal-heading">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>
                We rely on trusted third-party services to operate our website and deliver our services. Each provider has its
                own privacy practices:
            </p>

            <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
                <table class="legal-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Service</th>
                            <th>Purpose</th>
                            <th>Data Shared</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Microsoft Azure</strong></td>
                            <td>Hosting, cloud functions, storage, monitoring</td>
                            <td>Telemetry data, IP addresses, request logs</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Azure Application Insights</strong></td>
                            <td>Performance monitoring &amp; error diagnostics</td>
                            <td>Page views, session data, browser info, errors</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Anthropic (Claude AI)</strong></td>
                            <td>AI chatbot responses</td>
                            <td>Chatbot messages (processed in real time, not stored by us)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Brevo</strong></td>
                            <td>Transactional email delivery</td>
                            <td>Recipient email address, message content</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Google Calendar</strong></td>
                            <td>Appointment scheduling</td>
                            <td>Booking date, time, and timezone</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Google Fonts</strong></td>
                            <td>Typography</td>
                            <td>IP address (standard CDN request)</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <p>
                We encourage you to review the privacy policies of these services. We select providers that align with
                reasonable data protection standards.
            </p>

            @* ── 4. Cookies & Local Storage ── *@
            <h2 id="cookies" class="legal-heading">4. Cookies &amp; Local Storage</h2>
            <p>
                Our website uses minimal cookies and browser storage, limited to what is technically necessary:
            </p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>
                    <strong>Antiforgery Tokens</strong> — required by the application framework to protect against
                    cross-site request forgery attacks. These are session-scoped and expire when you close your browser.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Culture/Language Preference</strong> — if you switch languages, a cookie stores your preference
                    so it persists across page loads.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising cookies, social media tracking pixels, or third-party analytics
                cookies.
            </p>

            @* ── 5. Data Retention ── *@
            <h2 id="data-retention" class="legal-heading">5. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your information only as long as necessary for the purposes described:</p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>
                    <strong>Contact submissions</strong> — retained for up to 12 months to facilitate follow-up communication,
                    then deleted unless an ongoing business relationship exists.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Appointment bookings</strong> — retained for up to 90 days after the scheduled date.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Chatbot conversations</strong> — processed in real time and not persisted after your session ends.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Telemetry &amp; diagnostic logs</strong> — retained for up to 90 days in Azure Application
                    Insights, then automatically purged.
                </li>
            </ul>

            @* ── 6. Your Rights ── *@
            <h2 id="your-rights" class="legal-heading">6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
                Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:
            </p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.</li>
                <li><strong>Correction</strong> — request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion</strong> — request deletion of your personal information, subject to legal retention
                    requirements.</li>
                <li><strong>Opt-Out</strong> — opt out of non-essential data processing or communications.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
                <a href="mailto:info@cloud-zen.net" class="legal-link">info@cloud-zen.net</a>.
                We will respond to verified requests within 30 days.
            </p>

            @* ── 7. Children's Privacy ── *@
            <h2 id="childrens-privacy" class="legal-heading">7. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
                Our website and services are not directed at individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect
                personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact
                us and we will promptly delete it.
            </p>

            @* ── 8. Security ── *@
            <h2 id="security" class="legal-heading">8. Security</h2>
            <p>
                We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your information,
                including:
            </p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>HTTPS encryption for all data in transit.</li>
                <li>Strict security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options).</li>
                <li>Secrets managed through Azure Key Vault — never stored in source code.</li>
                <li>Input validation and rate limiting to prevent abuse.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot
                guarantee absolute security.
            </p>

            @* ── 9. Changes to This Policy ── *@
            <h2 id="changes" class="legal-heading">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last updated" date at the
                top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically. Continued use of the website after
                changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
            </p>

            @* ── 10. Contact Us ── *@
            <h2 id="contact" class="legal-heading">10. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your personal data, contact us at:
            </p>
            <address class="legal-address">
                <strong>CloudZen Inc.</strong><br />
                Email: <a href="mailto:info@cloud-zen.net" class="legal-link">info@cloud-zen.net</a><br />
                Website: <a href="https://www.cloud-zen.net" class="legal-link">cloud-zen.net</a>
            </address>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
